Commentary Text: Boult to Kohli, out Lbw!! Stunned! The crowd have been sushed into deathly silence at the Chinnaswamy. So plumb that Kohli walks off. Did not even look at du Plessis. The Boult trademark inswinger, pitches fuller on middle and Kohli plays all around the flick, misses, was going too square and the ball raps the pad. Michael Gough had the finger up in a flash and Boult is pumped. Generally he isn't but knows the importance of this wicket. What a start for RR. Kohli lbw b Boult 0(1)

Commentary Text: Siraj to Buttler, out Bowled!! Mohammed Siraj, what a champion he's become. He's bowled Buttler before in IPL. He knocks over the middle stump now. He bowls inswingers to LHBs and he sets up RHBs with the outswinger to bowl that cunning nip-backer. Buttler played outside the line looking for some movement away, but this beat the inside edge and smashed the leg stump. Without a proper inswinger to the right hander, Siraj is troubling the world with his scrambled seam ball, outswing, angle and the intent. What a story he is now. Buttler b Siraj 0(2)
